Generates/verifies the "tool contracts" doc block (between fixed HTML comment markers) in CLAUDE.md, template/CLAUDE.md, and README.md, sourced live from each binary's own `--contract` output rather than hand-written prose.

Usage: `gen_tool_contracts.sh [--write|--check] [ROOT]`; `--write` (default) rewrites the block in place, `--check` emits `FAIL:` lines in ctx-verify's format and sets exit code without modifying files — this is the mode ctx-verify's `contracts` battery check invokes.

Requires `ctx-context`, `ctx-verify`, `ctx-scan`, `ctx-cage`, `ctx-brief` already built and executable at `target/debug/`; never invokes cargo itself, so install-tools.sh (or manual `cargo build`) must run first, and missing binaries cause failure/FAIL rather than a build attempt.

`DOCS` list intentionally differs from `template/scripts/gen_tool_contracts.sh`: this repo's copy targets `CLAUDE.md`, `template/CLAUDE.md`, and `README.md`, while the template copy (synced into scaffolded projects) hardcodes just `CLAUDE.md` — a scaffolded project has no `template/` dir and its README documents the project, not this tooling. Do not merge these into one shared script.

Block boundaries are the literal strings in `$BEGIN`/`$END`; a doc missing either marker fails immediately. Content between markers is replaced wholesale via `awk`, never hand-edited — any manual edit there will be silently overwritten by `--write` or flagged stale by `--check`.